parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deformation and warping of the fuel tank can cause it to become loose and potentially lead to accidents, as it may disengage from its mounts and separate from the motorcycle.
symptoms: The fuel tank has warped or deformed
causing it to become loose from its mounts
the tank has expanded or spread
the tank has developed dimples or bubbles on its surface
the tank has lifted off the frame with minimal effort.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the motorcycle to stop running or not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The motorcycle stops running at any time
